-types of user in linux:
1. Root user: 
--> Root user is a super user in system who has all access pass to the system functinality.

2. Standard user:
--> standard user are those users which are created by root user and they have limited privileges compared to the root user.
eg: seema, amit

3. System user:
--> system user is a user account created by system rather than root user who used to run background processes and services.

