**Group Management**

1. groupadd <group_name>
--> used to create group
eg: groupadd AWS

2. groupdel <group_name>
--> used to delete group
eg: groupdel AWS

/etc/group : contains all group information

devops  :  x  :  5004  :
  1        2       3       4

  1: group name
  2: password
  3: group-id
  4: list of group members

*types of groups:
1. Primary Group:
--> this is default group assigned to the user at the time of account creation.
all files created by the user are associated with their primary group.

2. Secondary Group:
-->users can belong to additional group besides their primary group. called secondary group.

groupmod -n <new_groupname> <old_groupname>
--> to change/update a group name
groupmod -n testing AWS

usermod -aG <group_name> <user_name>
--> to append single user to group
usermod -aG aws seema 

gpasswd -d <user_name> <group_name>
--> to delete a user from group
gpasswd -d seema aws

gpasswd -M user_nm1,user_nm2.... <group_name>
---> to add multiple user to group
gpasswd -M seema,atul,meena  aws





